oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Oak Grove Methodist Church
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The Oak Grove Methodist Church, originally named the Oak Grove Methodist Episcopal Church South, was established in 1910 so that the residence of the Oak Grove region would not have to travel to neighboring communities to attend church services. The building was rebuilt in the 1930s and again in 1960 using the proceeds of sorghum molasses sales.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
